## 🚀 Reprioritized Roadmap (Execution Order)

1. Phase 3: Database Backup Automation
2. Phase 4: Observability and Alerting
3. Phase 7: Operational Readiness
4. Phase 5: Scalability and Performance
5. Phase 6: Testing and Quality Assurance
6. Phase 8: Architecture Refactor

Rationale: reliability and recovery capabilities must be in place before aggressive scaling and architecture changes.

---

## ☸ Kubernetes Deployment Instructions (Current State)

### 1) Deploy Core Platform (Phase 1)
```bash
kubectl apply -k infra/manifests/base
kubectl apply -k infra/manifests/overlays/production
```

### 2) Deploy Security Hardening (Phase 2)
```bash
bash scripts/deploy-phase2-security.sh
```

### 3) Deploy Database Backup Infrastructure (Phase 3)
```bash
bash scripts/deploy-phase3-database.sh
```

### 4) Verify Backup Infrastructure
```bash
kubectl -n koral-system get cronjobs | grep pgbackrest
kubectl -n koral-system get deployment pgbouncer
kubectl -n koral-system create job --from=cronjob/pgbackrest-full-backup pgbackrest-full-backup-manual
kubectl -n koral-system logs -f job/pgbackrest-full-backup-manual
```

### 5) Apply S3 Lifecycle Policy
```bash
aws s3api put-bucket-lifecycle-configuration \
  --bucket <your-backup-bucket> \
  --lifecycle-configuration file://infra/aws/s3-backup-lifecycle-policy.json
```

