## 🚀 Critical Path to Production (1–2 Weeks)

### Week 1: Infrastructure & Security

| Day | Task | Owner | Deliverable |
|-----|------|-------|-------------|
| Day 1–2 | Push images to Docker Hub / ECR with versioning | DevOps | Images with tags (v1.0.0, v1.0.1, etc.) |
| Day 2–3 | Setup TLS via cert-manager + Ingress | DevOps | HTTPS working on koral.example.com |
| Day 3–4 | Configure PostgreSQL backups to S3/GCS | DevOps | Daily backups, recovery tested |
| Day 4–5 | Deploy log aggregation (ELK or managed) | DevOps | Logs flowing to centralized service |
| Day 5–6 | Define alert rules + Slack/PagerDuty integration | SRE | Alerts firing correctly on test incidents |
| Day 6–7 | Implement K8s RBAC + NetworkPolicies | Security | Services can only communicate as designed |

### Week 2: Testing & Documentation

| Day | Task | Owner | Deliverable |
|-----|------|-------|-------------|
| Day 7–8 | Write automated E2E test suite | QA | Tests in CI/CD pipeline |
| Day 8–9 | Create Grafana dashboards | SRE | Team can view real-time metrics |
| Day 9–10 | Load testing & performance tuning | SRE | P95 latency < 200ms at 100 RPS |
| Day 10–11 | Document runbooks for common incidents | Ops | Playbooks for pod restart, failover, etc. |
| Day 11–12 | Train team & run production dry-run | Ops | Everyone can deploy and troubleshoot |
| Day 12–14 | Soft launch to staging; collect feedback | All | Known issues resolved before full launch |

