## 📋 Immediate Next Steps (Pick Any)

### Option A: Push to Production Registry
```bash
# Build and tag images
docker compose -f docker-compose-prod.yml build
docker tag koral-backend:latest your-registry/koral-backend:v1.0.0
docker tag koral-ai-engine:latest your-registry/koral-ai-engine:v1.0.0
docker tag koral-correlation-engine:latest your-registry/koral-correlation-engine:v1.0.0
docker tag koral-frontend:latest your-registry/koral-frontend:v1.0.0

# Push to registry
docker push your-registry/koral-backend:v1.0.0
docker push your-registry/koral-ai-engine:v1.0.0
docker push your-registry/koral-correlation-engine:v1.0.0
docker push your-registry/koral-frontend:v1.0.0

# Update K8s manifests with new image tags
sed -i 's|image: koral-backend:latest|image: your-registry/koral-backend:v1.0.0|g' k8s/*.yaml
```

### Option B: Setup TLS with Cert-Manager
```bash
# Install cert-manager
helm repo add jetstack https://charts.jetstack.io
helm install cert-manager jetstack/cert-manager --namespace cert-manager --create-namespace

# Update k8s/ingress.yaml with TLS configuration
# Apply Ingress with Let's Encrypt certificate
kubectl apply -f k8s/ingress.yaml
```

### Option C: Configure Prometheus Alerting
```yaml
# Add to prometheus.yml
alerting:
  alertmanagers:
    - static_configs:
        - targets: ['alertmanager:9093']

rule_files:
  - '/etc/prometheus/alert-rules.yml'
```

### Option D: Setup Database Backups
```bash
# Example: automated Postgres backup to S3
kubectl apply -f k8s/backup-cronjob.yaml  # Backs up postgres daily to S3
```

---

## ⚠️ Known Limitations & Risks

| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|------|----------|-----------|
| No auto-remediation yet | Medium | Implement K8s operator in Phase 3 |
| AI models not fine-tuned for your infra | Medium | Collect production incidents, retrain weekly |
| Single database replica (no HA) | High | Add read replicas, use RDS with Multi-AZ |
| Backup infrastructure generated but placeholders remain | High | Fill S3 credentials/bucket, validate PVC name, run manual backup and restore jobs |
| No log aggregation yet | High | Deploy ELK or Datadog before launch |
| Image registry setup may require org permissions | Medium | Validate ghcr.io permissions and image pull secrets |
| Certificate automation requires DNS/issuer validation | Medium | Verify ClusterIssuer and ingress domain ownership |
| Rate limiting policy tuning required | Medium | Load-test and tune by endpoint/user class |
| Monitoring incomplete (no alerting rules) | Medium | Define alert rules (Day 5–6) |

